snippet.textDisplay: I was 16 and just got my drivers license.  Driving my grandpas old K car (about the least cool car on the planet at the time). Traffic is stop and go headed north on the main st.  A beautiful girl stuck in the same traffic but headed south. Our cars align facing opposite directions.  She looks right at me, huge smile on her face and gives a flirty wave! I wave back, trying to play it cool.....her face immediately turns to a scowl and yells out “NOT YOU!”.  Apparently it was for some other kid she knew walking down the sidewalk on the other side of my car.
